==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Semiotics
<hw>Se`mi*ot"ics</hw> }</mhw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The study of signs as an element of communication; the analysis of
systems of communication; -- also called
<altname>semiology</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a theory of signs and symbols, including as branches
<er>semantics</er>, <er>pragmatics</er> and <er>syntactics</er>.</def>
<au>[RHUD]</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Semele</ent>⟦br⟧

